    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "98e2ecb5_f1bdc2da",
        "filename": "golden/modules/byblameentry-sk/byblameentry-sk_test.js",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-19T13:18:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When we have lots of hash-like data (which can blend together a bit), I sometimes doctor them up a bit (e.g. change the first three letters to aaa, bbb, 333, etc) so they can be quickly identified.  You don\u0027t have to do this for all of them, but just the \"important ones\" (for this, I\u0027d consider the commits as \"important\")\n\nAdditionally, for particularly unintuitive looking data that is depended on elswhere, it is  nice to have a comment (here, I might put \"The blame id is created/read server side as a colon separated list of commits\").",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 44,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 44,
        "endChar": 65
      },
